covered: Valid Request: Happy path (TC01) and combinations (TC02, TC05) verify 200 + application/json response.
Query parameters: offset/limit/audit are exercised (TC02-TC05) including invalid values (TC10-TC12) and extra params (TC18).
Empty responses: no-match, offset>total and empty DB cases covered (TC06, TC07, TC24).
Pagination boundaries: limit=0 and large-offset cases covered (TC07, TC08, TC26).
Audit levels: FULL and MINIMAL retrieval tested (TC03, TC04) and combined with pagination (TC05).
Authorization: missing and invalid tokens covered (TC13, TC14).
Error handling: malformed searchKey, injection attempt, server errors and dependency failures (TC09, TC15-TC17, TC25).
Performance & concurrency: large-volume and concurrent request tests included (TC19, TC20).
Search behavior: substring matching and partial DB scenarios covered (TC27, TC23).
Response semantics: tests assert correct status codes for success and common error cases per story ACs.
gaps: Caching behavior: no tests for Cache-Control, ETag, Last-Modified, If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since, or 304 flows.
Rate limiting/throttling: no tests for 429 responses, Retry-After headers, or sustained high-throughput behaviour.
Schema validation: Bundle object field-level schema (required fields, types, audit object structure) is not asserted.
Default parameter values: no explicit checks that omitting offset/limit/audit yields offset=0, limit=100, audit=NONE as per spec defaults.
Path encoding and reserved characters: searchKey containing "/", "?", spaces, non-ASCII, or very long strings (URL-encoding edge cases) not tested.
Missing path param / routing: no test for omitted searchKey path segment (expected 404/400 routing error).
Authorization nuance: missing tests for expired tokens, insufficient privileges (403), scopes or role-based access.
Content negotiation: Accept header variants and 406 Not Acceptable / response content negotiation not covered.
Pagination consistency & ordering: no verification that pagination yields deterministic, non-overlapping, stable ordering across pages (esp. under concurrent modifications).
Parameter type/format errors: strings for numeric params (e.g., offset=abc), floats, or numeric overflows are not tested.
Assumed limit caps: tests assume very large limits (TC26) but server-imposed maximums or protective rejection behavior are not validated.
recommendations: Add schema-level assertions for Bundle objects (required fields, types, nested audit structure) for FULL/MINIMAL/NONE.
Add explicit tests for default behaviours: when offset/limit/audit are omitted assert offset=0, limit=100, audit=NONE (and document server behavior).
Introduce caching tests: verify Cache-Control, ETag, Last-Modified headers; test If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since to get 304 responses.
Add rate-limiting tests: high-frequency requests to validate 429 and Retry-After semantics and that throttling is graceful.
Add path-encoding tests: searchKey with reserved chars, spaces, unicode, and very long values (and assert correct URL-encoding handling or proper 4xx failures).
Test missing/invalid routing (omitted path segment) to confirm expected 404/400 behaviour.
Expand auth tests: expired tokens, token scope/permission failures (403), and token format variants to cover more real-world auth failure modes.
Add content-negotiation tests (Accept header) and assert correct Content-Type and 406 handling for unsupported formats.
Add pagination consistency tests to assert stable ordering, no overlap/missing records across pages, and behaviour when underlying data changes.
Add type/format validation tests for query params (offset=abc, limit=1.5, extremely large integers) and clarify expected error codes.
Clarify and test server caps for limit/offset (if any); if server caps results, assert the cap and related response codes/headers (or document allowed maximum).
